lder\nno-hyphen clone (`stock-workspace/crypto-desk`, remote `.../cryptodesk`,\nconfig `~/.config/cryptodesk/`) is **archived** at\n`~/muthu/deemwarworkspace/_archive/cryptodesk-no-hyphen-OLD-2026-07-06` — do\nnot work there. (Prod on reqsume-app1 still tracks whatever its own clone\npoints at; verify before assuming it has moved to the hyphenated repo.)\nPer-machine runtime config (role local|prod, paths, owner-only risk\nenvelope, models) lives under that config dir. Architecture: 1-min close-only watchdog\n(cron) + cron-slotted headless Claude sessions (09:00 / 18:30 / 00:30 IST) +\nits own Telegram bot (listener `tg-listen` tmux) in the same ops chat + live\ndashboard at **https://cryptodesk.algofic.com** (cloudflared tunnel, tmux\n`cryptotunnel`). Repo skills (tracked in `.claude/skills/`): desk-ops,\ndesk-session, huddle-crypto, desk-retro, crypto-recon, crypto-backtest.\nHumans steer via `#cryptoloop` in Telegram as always.\n\n**Agent→desk (bots can't hear bots — Telegram sends from other agents do NOT\nreach the desk; use SSH):**\n\n```bash\n# send a message INTO the desk's inbox (any agent/session, any machine):\nssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'python3 -c \\\"\nimport json,sys,datetime\nline=json.dumps({\\\\\\\"ts\\\\\\\":datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()+\\\\\\\"Z\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"from\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"AGENT_NAME\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"tag\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"cryptoloop\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"#cryptoloop MESSAGE\\\\\\\"})\nopen(\\\\\\\"/home/stockwork/.config/agent-telegram/sessions/cryptoloop/inbox.ndjson\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"a\\\\\\\").write(line+chr(10))\\\"'\"\n\n# look at the desk (state, health, last actions):\nssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'cat ~/crypto-desk/artifacts/crypto/positions-state.json; tail -5 ~/crypto-desk/logs/watchdog.log; ls -t ~/crypto-desk/logs/session-*.log | head -1 | xargs tail -20'\"\n\n# kill switch / restart:\nssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'touch ~/crypto-desk/STOP'\"      # halt (venue brackets stay live)\nssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'rm -f ~/crypto-desk/STOP'\"      # re-arm\nssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'cd ~/crypto-desk && bash scripts/boot.sh'\"  # re-boot everything (idempotent)\n```\n\nSaying \"stop/halt/flatten\" on `#cryptoloop` (as a human) also engages the kill\nswitch via the watchdog. Stock loops (NSE/BSE) remain on the local Mac — Phase 2\nmoves them the same way once crypto-on-prod earns confidence.\n\n### Shared platform on prod (reqsume-app1) — messenger + browser-bridge\n\nBoth run as `systemd --user` services under `stockwork` (boot-start via\n`loginctl enable-linger`), bound to localhost, so **any agent/process on the\nbox** reaches them over plain HTTP — one hub / one bridge per host, shared by\nevery desk (crypto, CEO, whatever else lands there).\n\n- **messenger** (`:14310`) — the channel hub (WhatsApp/Telegram/webhook).\n  Health: `curl http://127.0.0.1:14310/health` → `{\"channels\":{...},\"ok\":true}`.\n  WhatsApp device is linked once per host; the crypto desk's channel is\n  `cryptodesk` → the same `#cryptoloop` group JID (`120363410186820001@g.us`)\n  as the local Mac's hub, paired 2026-07-06.\n  Restart: `ssh reqsume-app1 \"su -l stockwork -c 'export XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/\\$(id -u); systemctl --user restart messenger'\"`\n  Self-updates daily (git-pull → rebuild static → atomic swap → restart) via\n  a `messenger-selfupdate` script + systemd `--user` timer; log at\n  `~/.config/messenger/selfupdate.log`.\n- **browser-bridge** (`:8779`) — headless research browser. Runs **Brave**,\n  not Chrome — Chrome 137+/150 dropped the `--load-extension` flag the bridge\n  extension needs, Brave still honors it. Lives on Xvfb `:101` with a\n  logged-in profile copied over from the Mac (local alias `brave-desk` opens\n  that same dedicated profile — `open -na \"Brave Browser\" --args\n  --user-data-dir=~/.config/browser-research/profile` — log into sites there,\n  then tar+scp to prod's `~/.config/browser-research/profile`).